From: Andrew Lennon <andrew.lennon@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: tas6424: linear CH1-4 volume controls (no TLV dB)

SOC_SINGLE_TLV maps register 0-255 through a dB TLV curve, so alsamixer
shows dB labels and cset 20 != sset 20% (lab confusion). Use SOC_SINGLE
so amixer/alsamixer number = hardware register = cset value.

Requires 0026 (Tannoy CHn names). Lab default index 20 (~8% of max);
previously TLV 20% used register ~51.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Lennon <andrew.lennon@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c | 13 ++++++-------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c b/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c
index 2222222..3333333 100644
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c
@@ -55,16 +55,14 @@
 #define TAS6424_LDGBYPASS_SHIFT		7
 #define TAS6424_LDGBYPASS_MASK		BIT(7)
 
-static DECLARE_TLV_DB_SCALE(dac_tlv, -10350, 50, 0);
-
 static const struct snd_kcontrol_new tas6424_snd_controls[] = {
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH1 Playback Volume",
-		       TAS6424_CH1_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH2 Playback Volume",
-		       TAS6424_CH2_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH3 Playback Volume",
-		       TAS6424_CH3_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH4 Playback Volume",
-		       TAS6424_CH4_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
+	SOC_SINGLE("Tannoy CH1 Playback Volume",
+		   TAS6424_CH1_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0),
+	SOC_SINGLE("Tannoy CH2 Playback Volume",
+		   TAS6424_CH2_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0),
+	SOC_SINGLE("Tannoy CH3 Playback Volume",
+		   TAS6424_CH3_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0),
+	SOC_SINGLE("Tannoy CH4 Playback Volume",
+		   TAS6424_CH4_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0),
 	SOC_SINGLE_STROBE("Auto Diagnostics Switch", TAS6424_DC_DIAG_CTRL1,
 			  TAS6424_LDGBYPASS_SHIFT, 1),
